                             17:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             18:package org.apache.poi.hslf.dev;                                                                                                                                                 
                             19:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             20:import org.apache.poi.ddf.DefaultEscherRecordFactory;                                                                                                                            
                             21:import org.apache.poi.ddf.EscherContainerRecord;                                                                                                                                 
                             22:import org.apache.poi.ddf.EscherRecord;                                                                                                                                          
                             23:import org.apache.poi.ddf.EscherTextboxRecord;                                                                                                                                   
                             24:import org.apache.poi.hslf.record.HSLFEscherRecordFactory;                                                                                                                       
                             25:import org.apache.poi.hslf.record.RecordTypes;                                                                                                                                   
                             26:import org.apache.poi.hslf.usermodel.HSLFSlideShow;                                                                                                                              
                             27:import org.apache.poi.poifs.filesystem.POIFSFileSystem;                                                                                                                          
                             28:import org.apache.poi.util.HexDump;                                                                                                                                              
                             29:import org.apache.poi.util.IOUtils;                                                                                                                                              
                             30:import org.apache.poi.util.LittleEndian;                                                                                                                                         
                             31:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             32:import java.io.File;                                                                                                                                                             
                             33:import java.io.IOException;                                                                                                                                                      
                             34:import java.io.InputStream;                                                                                                                                                      
                             35:import java.io.PrintStream;                                                                                                                                                      
                             36:import java.util.Locale;                                                                                                                                                         
                             37:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             38:/**                                                                                                                                                                              
                             39: * This class provides a way to "peek" inside a powerpoint file. It                                                                                                              
                             40: * will print out all the types it finds, and for those it knows aren't                                                                                                          
                             41: * atoms, what they contain                                                                                                                                                      
                             42: * <p>                                                                                                                                                                           
                             43: * To figure out what things are, and if they are atoms or not, used the                                                                                                         
                             44: * list in hslf.record.RecordTypes                                                                                                                                               
                             45: * <p>                                                                                                                                                                           
                             46: * To peek inside PPDrawings, which hold Escher drawings, we use the                                                                                                             
                             47: * DDF package from POI (but we can fake it by using the Escher listings                                                                                                         
                             48: * from hslf.record.RecordTypes also)                                                                                                                                            
                             49: */                                                                                                                                                                              
                             50:public final class SlideShowDumper {                                                                                                                                             
                             51:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             52:    //arbitrarily selected; may need to increase                                                                                                                                 
                             53:    private static final int DEFAULT_MAX_RECORD_LENGTH = 100_000;                                                                                                                
                             54:    private static int MAX_RECORD_LENGTH = DEFAULT_MAX_RECORD_LENGTH;                                                                                                            
                             55:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             56:    private byte[] docstream;                                                                                                                                                    
                             57:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             58:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             59:     * Do we try to use DDF to understand the escher objects?                                                                                                                    
                             60:     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                             61:    private boolean ddfEscher;                                                                                                                                                   
                             62:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             63:     * Do we use our own built-in basic escher groker to understand the escher objects?                                                                                          
                             64:     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                             65:    private boolean basicEscher;                                                                                                                                                 
                             66:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             67:    private PrintStream out;                                                                                                                                                     
                             68:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             69:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             70:     * @param length the max record length allowed for SlideShowDumper                                                                                                           
                             71:     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                             72:    public static void setMaxRecordLength(int length) {                                                                                                                          
                             73:        MAX_RECORD_LENGTH = length;                                                                                                                                              
                             74:    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                             75:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             76:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             77:     * @return the max record length allowed for SlideShowDumper                                                                                                                 
                             78:     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                             79:    public static int getMaxRecordLength() {                                                                                                                                     
                             80:        return MAX_RECORD_LENGTH;                                                                                                                                                
                             81:    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                             82:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             83:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             84:     * right now this function takes one parameter: a ppt file, and outputs                                                                                                      
                             85:     * a dump of what it contains                                                                                                                                                
                             86:     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                             87:    public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {                                                                                                                  
                             88:        if (args.length == 0) {                                                                                                                                                  
                             89:            System.err.println("Usage: SlideShowDumper [-escher|-basicescher] <filename>");                                                                                      
                             90:            return;                                                                                                                                                              
                             91:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             92:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             93:        String filename = args[0];                                                                                                                                               
                             94:        if (args.length > 1) {                                                                                                                                                   
                             95:            filename = args[1];                                                                                                                                                  
                             96:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             97:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             98:        try (POIFSFileSystem poifs = new POIFSFileSystem(new File(filename))) {                                                                                                  
                             99:            SlideShowDumper foo = new SlideShowDumper(poifs, System.out);                                                                                                        
                             100:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             101:            if (args.length > 1) {                                                                                                                                              
                             102:                if (args[0].equalsIgnoreCase("-escher")) {                                                                                                                      
                             103:                    foo.setDDFEscher(true);                                                                                                                                     
                             104:                } else {                                                                                                                                                        
                             105:                    foo.setBasicEscher(true);                                                                                                                                   
                             106:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             107:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             108:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             109:            foo.printDump();                                                                                                                                                    
                             110:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             111:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             112:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             113:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             114:     * Constructs a Powerpoint dump from a POIFS Filesystem. Parses the                                                                                                         
                             115:     * document and dumps out the contents                                                                                                                                      
                             116:     *                                                                                                                                                                          
                             117:     * @param filesystem the POIFS FileSystem to read from                                                                                                                      
                             118:     * @throws IOException if there is a problem while parsing the document.                                                                                                    
                             119:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             120:    public SlideShowDumper(POIFSFileSystem filesystem, PrintStream out) throws IOException {                                                                                    
                             121:        // Grab the document stream                                                                                                                                             
                             122:        InputStream is = filesystem.createDocumentInputStream(HSLFSlideShow.POWERPOINT_DOCUMENT);                                                                               
                             123:        docstream = IOUtils.toByteArray(is);                                                                                                                                    
                             124:        is.close();                                                                                                                                                             
                             125:        this.out = out;                                                                                                                                                         
                             126:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             127:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             128:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             129:     * Control dumping of any Escher records found - should DDF be used?                                                                                                        
                             130:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             131:    public void setDDFEscher(boolean grok) {                                                                                                                                    
                             132:        ddfEscher = grok;                                                                                                                                                       
                             133:        basicEscher = !(grok);                                                                                                                                                  
                             134:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             135:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             136:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             137:     * Control dumping of any Escher records found - should our built in                                                                                                        
                             138:     * basic groker be used?                                                                                                                                                    
                             139:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             140:    public void setBasicEscher(boolean grok) {                                                                                                                                  
                             141:        basicEscher = grok;                                                                                                                                                     
                             142:        ddfEscher = !(grok);                                                                                                                                                    
                             143:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             144:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             145:    public void printDump() throws IOException {                                                                                                                                
                             146:        // The format of records in a powerpoint file are:                                                                                                                      
                             147:        //   <little endian 2 byte "info">                                                                                                                                      
                             148:        //   <little endian 2 byte "type">                                                                                                                                      
                             149:        //   <little endian 4 byte "length">                                                                                                                                    
                             150:        // If it has a zero length, following it will be another record                                                                                                         
                             151:        //      <xx xx yy yy 00 00 00 00> <xx xx yy yy zz zz zz zz>                                                                                                             
                             152:        // If it has a length, depending on its type it may have children or data                                                                                               
                             153:        // If it has children, these will follow straight away                                                                                                                  
                             154:        //      <xx xx yy yy zz zz zz zz <xx xx yy yy zz zz zz zz>>                                                                                                             
                             155:        // If it has data, this will come straight after, and run for the length                                                                                                
                             156:        //      <xx xx yy yy zz zz zz zz dd dd dd dd dd dd dd>                                                                                                                  
                             157:        // All lengths given exclude the 8 byte record header                                                                                                                   
                             158:        // (Data records are known as Atoms)                                                                                                                                    
                             159:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             160:        // Document should start with:                                                                                                                                          
                             161:        //   0F 00 E8 03 ## ## ## ##                                                                                                                                            
                             162:        //     (type 1000 = document, info 00 0f is normal, rest is document length)                                                                                            
                             163:        //   01 00 E9 03 28 00 00 00                                                                                                                                            
                             164:        //     (type 1001 = document atom, info 00 01 normal, 28 bytes long)                                                                                                    
                             165:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             166:        // When parsing a document, look to see if you know about that type                                                                                                     
                             167:        //  of the current record. If you know it's a type that has children,                                                                                                   
                             168:        //  process the record's data area looking for more records                                                                                                             
                             169:        // If you know about the type and it doesn't have children, either do                                                                                                   
                             170:        //  something with the data (eg TextRun) or skip over it                                                                                                                
                             171:        // Otherwise, check the first byte. If you do a BINARY_AND on it with                                                                                                   
                             172:        //  0x0f (15) and get back 0x0f, you know it has children. Otherwise                                                                                                    
                             173:        //  it doesn't                                                                                                                                                          
                             174:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             175:        walkTree(0, 0, docstream.length);                                                                                                                                       
                             176:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             177:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             178:    public void walkTree(int depth, int startPos, int maxLen) throws IOException {                                                                                              
                             179:        int pos = startPos;                                                                                                                                                     
                             180:        int endPos = startPos + maxLen;                                                                                                                                         
                             181:        final String ind = (depth == 0) ? "%1$s" : "%1$" + depth + "s";                                                                                                         
                             182:        while (pos <= endPos - 8) {                                                                                                                                             
                             183:            long type = LittleEndian.getUShort(docstream, pos + 2);                                                                                                             
                             184:            long len = LittleEndian.getUInt(docstream, pos + 4);                                                                                                                
                             185:            byte opt = docstream[pos];                                                                                                                                          
                             186:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             187:            String fmt = ind + "At position %2$d (%2$04x): type is %3$d (%3$04x), len is %4$d (%4$04x)";                                                                        
                             188:            out.printf(Locale.ROOT, (fmt) + "%n", "", pos, type, len);                                                                                                          
                             189:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             190:            // See if we know about the type of it                                                                                                                              
                             191:            String recordName = RecordTypes.forTypeID((short) type).name();                                                                                                     
                             192:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             193:            // Jump over header, and think about going on more                                                                                                                  
                             194:            pos += 8;                                                                                                                                                           
                             195:            out.printf(Locale.ROOT, ind + "That's a %2$s%n", "", recordName);                                                                                                   
                             196:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             197:            if (len < 0 /*|| len > Integer.MAX_VALUE*/) {                                                                                                                       
                             198:                // stop processing of invalid header data                                                                                                                       
                             199:                continue;                                                                                                                                                       
                             200:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hslf/dev/SlideShowDumper.java:178-200                                                                                                   
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             178:    public void walkTree(int depth, int startPos, int maxLen) throws IOException {                                                                                              
                             179:        int pos = startPos;                                                                                                                                                     
                             180:        int endPos = startPos + maxLen;                                                                                                                                         
                             181:        final String ind = (depth == 0) ? "%1$s" : "%1$" + depth + "s";                                                                                                         
                             182:        while (pos <= endPos - 8) {                                                                                                                                             
                             183:            long type = LittleEndian.getUShort(docstream, pos + 2);                                                                                                             
                             184:            long len = LittleEndian.getUInt(docstream, pos + 4);                                                                                                                
                             185:            byte opt = docstream[pos];                                                                                                                                          
                             186:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             187:            String fmt = ind + "At position %2$d (%2$04x): type is %3$d (%3$04x), len is %4$d (%4$04x)";                                                                        
                             188:            out.printf(Locale.ROOT, (fmt) + "%n", "", pos, type, len);                                                                                                          
                             189:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             190:            // See if we know about the type of it                                                                                                                              
                             191:            String recordName = RecordTypes.forTypeID((short) type).name();                                                                                                     
                             192:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             193:            // Jump over header, and think about going on more                                                                                                                  
                             194:            pos += 8;                                                                                                                                                           
                             195:            out.printf(Locale.ROOT, ind + "That's a %2$s%n", "", recordName);                                                                                                   
                             196:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             197:            if (len < 0 /*|| len > Integer.MAX_VALUE*/) {                                                                                                                       
                             198:                // stop processing of invalid header data                                                                                                                       
                             199:                continue;                                                                                                                                                       
                             200:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hslf/dev/PPTXMLDump.java:124-132                                                                                                        
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             124:            int size = (int)LittleEndian.getUInt(data, pos);                                                                                                                    
                             125:            pos += LittleEndianConsts.INT_SIZE;                                                                                                                                 
                             126:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             127:            if (size < 0) {                                                                                                                                                     
                             128:                // stop processing of invalid header data                                                                                                                       
                             129:                continue;                                                                                                                                                       
                             130:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             131:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             132:            //get name of the record by type                                                                                                                                    
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             </code_snippets>                                                                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Root Cause Analysis                                                                                                                                                              
                                - The dump loop in PPTXMLDump.java advances `pos` by the 8byte header (2 bytes info + 2 bytes type + 4 bytes size), then recurses on container records and                      
                             finally does `pos += size`.                                                                                                                                                         
                                - When `size == 0`, the code recurses on an empty subrange (immediately returns), then does `pos += 0`, leaving `pos` unchanged at headerEnd. The whileloop                     
                             condition still holds, producing an infinite loop and thus a libFuzzer timeout.                                                                                                     
                                - Previous patch only guarded against `size < 0` or `size > remaining`, but missed `size == 0`.                                                                                  
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Patch Strategy                                                                                                                                                                   
                                - Modify the headersize check in the main `while` loop of `PPTXMLDump.dump(byte[], ...)`:                                                                                       
                                  a) Preserve the existing guard against negative sizes (skip invalid headers using `continue`).                                                                                 
                                  b) Introduce an explicit check for zerolength records (`size == 0`) and break out of the main loop to prevent infinite loops.                                                 
                                  c) Retain the boundscheck for `size > remaining` and break in that case as before.                                                                                            
                                - Implementation sketch (in place of lines 126132):                                                                                                                             
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                      int size = (int)LittleEndian.getUInt(data, pos);                                                                                                                           
                                      pos += LittleEndianConsts.INT_SIZE;                                                                                                                                        
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                      // 1) Negative size: skip record                                                                                                                                           
                                      if (size < 0) {                                                                                                                                                            
                                          continue;                                                                                                                                                              
                                      }                                                                                                                                                                          
                                      // 2) Zero size: avoid infinite loop by aborting further processing                                                                                                        
                                      if (size == 0) {                                                                                                                                                           
                                          break;                                                                                                                                                                 
                                      }                                                                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                      // 3) Size larger than remaining buffer: abort processing safely                                                                                                           
                                      int remaining = offset + length - pos;                                                                                                                                     
                                      if (size > remaining) {                                                                                                                                                    
                                          break;                                                                                                                                                                 
                                      }                                                                                                                                                                          
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                - No other loops or recursion in PPTXMLDump are impacted; the remainder of the recordprocessing logic remains intact, preserving correct dumps for wellformed                  
                             PPT streams.                                                                                                                                                                        
                                - This patch will stop the dump loop as soon as a zerolength or malformed record is encountered, exiting gracefully instead of hanging.                                         
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Preservation of Functionality                                                                                                                                                    
                                - Valid, positivelength records continue to be processed and dumped as before.                                                                                                  
                                - Negative sizes continue to be skipped (consistent with original codes intent to ignore obviously invalid headers).                                                            
                                - The new zerolength check only affects pathological container records leading to infinite loops; real PPT data use nonzero container lengths.                                 
                                - Boundscheck behavior (`size > remaining`) remains unchanged from the last patch.                                                                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. SideEffect Mitigation                                                                                                                                                           
                                - Breaking on zerolength container records stops dumping further records in the same stream. In production use, encountering a zerolength container in                         
                             PPTXMLDump likely indicates corrupt or malicious data; aborting is safer than hanging.                                                                                              
                                - If downstream code expects to skip zerolength containers rather than abort, we could alternatively `continue` and manually advance `pos` by `HEADER_SIZE`but                 
                             given the fuzzer context, immediate loop exit is acceptable.                                                                                                                        
                                - No tests or harness code are modified, so existing unit tests and the libFuzzer harness continue operating unchanged.                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. Implementation Steps                                                                                                                                                             
                                1. Open `poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hslf/dev/PPTXMLDump.java`.                                                                                                  
                                2. Locate the main loop starting at line ~112 and find the headersize block at lines 124132.                                                                                   
                                3. Replace the `if (size < 0)  continue;` and subsequent `remaining`bounds check with the code snippet described above.                                                        
                                4. Recompile and rerun `mvn test` to verify no regressions.                                                                                                                      
                                5. Reexecute the libFuzzer harness to confirm the timeout no longer occurs.                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             6. Justification                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - Directly addresses the infiniteloop symptom (libFuzzer timeout) by ensuring `pos` cannot stall because of a zerolength record.                                               
                                - Aligns with patterns in other dump utilities (e.g., SlideShowDumper), which likewise break on nonsensical lengths.                                                             
                                - Minimal intrusiveness, only touching the narrow scope of the headersize logic in PPTXMLDump.                                                                                  
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                     
                             ===Evaluation End===

                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Summary                                                                                                                                                                          
                             The projects fuzzy testing harness reported a libFuzzer timeout when exercising the PPTXMLDump code path. In response, a patch was applied to `PPTXMLDump.java`                    
                             that adds three new sizechecks in the recordparsing loop:                                                                                                                         
                             1. Skip records with negative size                                                                                                                                                  
                             2. Break out on zero size                                                                                                                                                           
                             3. Break out when declared size exceeds remaining buffer space                                                                                                                      
                             After rebuilding with these guards, the harness still produces a libFuzzer timeout error.                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Description                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Initial Issue                                                                                                                                                                       
                             - When running under libFuzzer, the code path in `org.apache.poi.hslf.dev.PPTXMLDump` does not terminate within the allotted time and triggers a timeout error.                   
                             - No exceptions or crashes are reportedonly an overall hang or excessively long processing cycle.                                                                                  
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Important Observations                                                                                                                                                              
                             - The timeout suggests an infinite or very long loop in the recordparsing logic.                                                                                                   
                             - The existing loop reads a 4byte unsigned size field (`LittleEndian.getUInt`) and then processes that many bytes; malformed or unexpected values can cause the                    
                             loop to never exit or to perform excessive work.                                                                                                                                    
                             - The fuzzer harness itself is not identified as the root cause; it merely drives input into the vulnerable code.                                                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Patch Attempt                                                                                                                                                                       
                             The patch modifies the recordreading loop in `PPTXMLDump.java` at approximately line 124:                                                                                          
                               1. After reading `size` and advancing `pos`, it continues the loop if `size < 0`.                                                                                                 
                               2. If `size == 0`, it breaks the loop to prevent an infinite loop on zero-length records.                                                                                         
                               3. It computes `remaining = offset + length - pos`; if `size > remaining`, it breaks the loop to avoid overrunning the buffer.                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             The patch in unified diff form:                                                                                                                                                     
                             --- a/poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hslf/dev/PPTXMLDump.java                                                                                                          
                             +++ b/poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hslf/dev/PPTXMLDump.java                                                                                                          
                             @@ -124,9 +124,18 @@                                                                                                                                                                
                                          int size = (int)LittleEndian.getUInt(data, pos);                                                                                                                       
                                          pos += LittleEndianConsts.INT_SIZE;                                                                                                                                    
                             +            // 1) Negative size: skip record                                                                                                                                       
                                          if (size < 0) {                                                                                                                                                        
                             -                // stop processing of invalid header data                                                                                                                          
                                              continue;                                                                                                                                                          
                             +            }                                                                                                                                                                      
                             +            // 2) Zero size: avoid infinite loop by aborting further processing                                                                                                    
                             +            if (size == 0) {                                                                                                                                                       
                             +                break;                                                                                                                                                             
                             +            }                                                                                                                                                                      
                             +            // 3) Size larger than remaining buffer: abort processing safely                                                                                                       
                             +            int remaining = offset + length - pos;                                                                                                                                 
                             +            if (size > remaining) {                                                                                                                                                
                             +                break;                                                                                                                                                             
                                          }                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             After applying this patch and rebuilding, the fuzzer still reports:                                                                                                                 
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Areas for Further Investigation                                                                                                                                                     
                             - The remainder of the recordparsing loop around `pos` advancement and actual record consumptionverify that all code paths advance `pos` and eventually exit.                     
                             - Any nested loops or recursive calls invoked after header parsing (e.g., sub-record parsing, property tables).                                                                     
                             - Other datadriven loops in `PPTXMLDump` that may not include adequate termination checks.                                                                                         
                             - The initial boundaries: the values of `offset`, `length`, and how they are computed/passed into the loop.                                                                         
                             - Surrounding methods that call the patched loop to ensure no external factors reinitialize or prolong processing.                                                                  
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Initial Issue Log                                                                                                                                                                
                             Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                                                                                                                      
                             <issue>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </issue>                                                                                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Additional Issue Log                                                                                                                                                             
                             Here is the additional issue log after the last patch attempt:                                                                                                                      
                             <additional_issue>                                                                                                                                                                  
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </additional_issue>                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Notes                                                                                                                                                                            
                             - All patch attempts are applied to the initial codebase. Reapply the the previous patches if needed.                                                                               
                             - If multiple different issues are present, all the issues must be resolved in a single patch attempt.                                                                              
                             - Try different approaches to resolve the issues.                                                                                                                                   
                             ===Analysis Report===                                                                                                                                                               
                             # Analysis Report                                                                                                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Relevant Code Snippets                                                                                                                                                           
                             <code_snippets>                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <code>
