                             34:import org.apache.poi.hslf.usermodel.HSLFSlideShow;                                                                                                                              
                             35:import org.apache.poi.poifs.filesystem.DirectoryNode;                                                                                                                            
                             36:import org.apache.poi.poifs.filesystem.POIFSFileSystem;                                                                                                                          
                             37:import org.apache.poi.util.IOUtils;                                                                                                                                              
                             38:import org.apache.poi.util.LittleEndian;                                                                                                                                         
                             39:import org.apache.poi.util.LittleEndianConsts;                                                                                                                                   
                             40:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             41:/**                                                                                                                                                                              
                             42: * Utility class which dumps raw contents of a ppt file into XML format                                                                                                          
                             43: */                                                                                                                                                                              
                             44:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             45:public final class PPTXMLDump {                                                                                                                                                  
                             46:    private static final int HEADER_SIZE = 8; //size of the record header                                                                                                        
                             47:    private static final int PICT_HEADER_SIZE = 25; //size of the picture header                                                                                                 
                             48:    private static final String PICTURES_ENTRY = "Pictures";                                                                                                                     
                             49:    private static final String CR = System.getProperty("line.separator");                                                                                                       
                             50:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             51:    private Writer out;                                                                                                                                                          
                             52:    private final byte[] docstream;                                                                                                                                              
                             53:    private final byte[] pictstream;                                                                                                                                             
                             54:    private final boolean hexHeader = true;                                                                                                                                      
                             55:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             56:    public PPTXMLDump(File ppt) throws IOException {                                                                                                                             
                             57:        try (POIFSFileSystem fs = new POIFSFileSystem(ppt, true)) {                                                                                                              
                             58:            docstream = readEntry(fs, HSLFSlideShow.POWERPOINT_DOCUMENT);                                                                                                        
                             59:            pictstream = readEntry(fs, PICTURES_ENTRY);                                                                                                                          
                             60:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hslf/dev/PPTXMLDump.java:112-132                                                                                                        
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             112:    public void dump(byte[] data, int offset, int length, int padding) throws IOException {                                                                                     
                             113:        int pos = offset;                                                                                                                                                       
                             114:        while (pos <= (offset + length - HEADER_SIZE)){                                                                                                                         
                             115:            if (pos < 0) {                                                                                                                                                      
                             116:                break;                                                                                                                                                          
                             117:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             118:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             119:            //read record header                                                                                                                                                
                             120:            int info = LittleEndian.getUShort(data, pos);                                                                                                                       
                             121:            pos += LittleEndianConsts.SHORT_SIZE;                                                                                                                               
                             122:            int type = LittleEndian.getUShort(data, pos);                                                                                                                       
                             123:            pos += LittleEndianConsts.SHORT_SIZE;                                                                                                                               
                             124:            int size = (int)LittleEndian.getUInt(data, pos);                                                                                                                    
                             125:            pos += LittleEndianConsts.INT_SIZE;                                                                                                                                 
                             126:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             127:            if (size < 0) {                                                                                                                                                     
                             128:                // stop processing of invalid header data                                                                                                                       
                             129:                continue;                                                                                                                                                       
                             130:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             131:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             132:            //get name of the record by type                                                                                                                                    
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hslf/dev/PPTXMLDump.java:133-156                                                                                                        
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             133:            String recname = RecordTypes.forTypeID(type).name();                                                                                                                
                             134:            write(out, "<"+recname + " info=\""+info+"\" type=\""+type+"\" size=\""+size+"\" offset=\""+(pos-8)+"\"", padding);                                                 
                             135:            if (hexHeader){                                                                                                                                                     
                             136:                out.write(" header=\"");                                                                                                                                        
                             137:                dump(out, data, pos-8, 8, 0, false);                                                                                                                            
                             138:                out.write("\"");                                                                                                                                                
                             139:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             140:            out.write(">" + CR);                                                                                                                                                
                             141:            padding++;                                                                                                                                                          
                             142:            //this check works both for Escher and PowerPoint records                                                                                                           
                             143:            boolean isContainer = (info & 0x000F) == 0x000F;                                                                                                                    
                             144:            if (isContainer) {                                                                                                                                                  
                             145:                //continue to dump child records                                                                                                                                
                             146:                dump(data, pos, size, padding);                                                                                                                                 
                             147:            } else {                                                                                                                                                            
                             148:                //dump first 100 bytes of the atom data                                                                                                                         
                             149:                dump(out, data, pos, Math.min(size, data.length-pos), padding, true);                                                                                           
                             150:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             151:            padding--;                                                                                                                                                          
                             152:            write(out, "</"+recname + ">" + CR, padding);                                                                                                                       
                             153:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             154:            pos += size;                                                                                                                                                        
                             155:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             156:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hslf/dev/PPTXMLDump.java:253-271                                                                                                        
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             253:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             254:     *  dump binary data to {@code out} with the specified padding                                                                                                              
                             255:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             256:    private static void dump(Writer out, byte[] data, int offset, int length, int padding, boolean nl) throws IOException {                                                     
                             257:        int linesize = 25;                                                                                                                                                      
                             258:        for (int i = 0; i < padding; i++) out.write("  ");                                                                                                                      
                             259:        int i;                                                                                                                                                                  
                             260:        for (i = offset; i < (offset + length); i++) {                                                                                                                          
                             261:            int c = data[i];                                                                                                                                                    
                             262:            out.write((char) hexval[(c & 0xF0) >> 4]);                                                                                                                          
                             263:            out.write((char) hexval[(c & 0x0F) >> 0]);                                                                                                                          
                             264:            out.write(' ');                                                                                                                                                     
                             265:            if((i+1-offset) % linesize == 0 && i != (offset + length-1)) {                                                                                                      
                             266:                out.write(CR);                                                                                                                                                  
                             267:                for (int j = 0; j < padding; j++) out.write("  ");                                                                                                              
                             268:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             269:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             270:        if(nl && length > 0)out.write(CR);                                                                                                                                      
                             271:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             </code_snippets>                                                                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Restore syntax integrity in PPTXMLDump.java by removing the malformed overloaded `dump(OutputStream, byte[], , boolean hex)` stub that introduced unmatched                     
                             Javadoc markers and misplaced braces. The existing private static `dump(Writer,out)` helper suffices; no new overload is needed.                                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Introduce a classlevel constant near the top of PPTXMLDump.java:                                                                                                                
                                ```                                                                                                                                                                              
                                private static final int MAX_DUMP = 1024;                                                                                                                                        
                                ```                                                                                                                                                                              
                                This centralizes the maximum bytedump cap and avoids magic numbers.                                                                                                             
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Harden the primary binaryrecord dump method (`public void dump(byte[] data, int offset, int length, int padding)`):                                                             
                                a. At the start of the `while (pos <= offset + length - HEADER_SIZE)` loop, insert:                                                                                              
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                   int remaining = offset + length - pos;                                                                                                                                        
                                   if (remaining < HEADER_SIZE) {                                                                                                                                                
                                       break;                                                                                                                                                                    
                                   }                                                                                                                                                                             
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                b. Change the existing `if (size < 0)` branch to:                                                                                                                                
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                   if (size <= 0) {                                                                                                                                                              
                                       break;                                                                                                                                                                    
                                   }                                                                                                                                                                             
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                c. Immediately after reading `size`, insert:                                                                                                                                     
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                   if (size > remaining) {                                                                                                                                                       
                                       break;                                                                                                                                                                    
                                   }                                                                                                                                                                             
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                These changes ensure we never read past the buffer or spin on zerolength records.                                                                                               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Cap the amount of atom data hexdumped per record by modifying the existing call:                                                                                                
                                Replace                                                                                                                                                                          
                                ```                                                                                                                                                                              
                                dump(out, data, pos, Math.min(size, data.length - pos), padding, true);                                                                                                          
                                ```                                                                                                                                                                              
                                with                                                                                                                                                                             
                                ```                                                                                                                                                                              
                                dump(out, data, pos,                                                                                                                                                             
                                     Math.min(size, Math.min(data.length - pos, MAX_DUMP)),                                                                                                                      
                                     padding, true);                                                                                                                                                             
                                ```                                                                                                                                                                              
                                This preserves the existing hexdump helper and enforces the 1024byte limit.                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. In the `dumpPictures(byte[] data, int padding)` method, similarly cap picture image dumps:                                                                                       
                                Replace                                                                                                                                                                          
                                ```                                                                                                                                                                              
                                dump(out, data, 0, Math.min(size, 100), padding, true);                                                                                                                          
                                ```                                                                                                                                                                              
                                with                                                                                                                                                                             
                                ```                                                                                                                                                                              
                                dump(out, data, 0, Math.min(size, MAX_DUMP), padding, true);                                                                                                                     
                                ```                                                                                                                                                                              
                                This applies a uniform cap and removes arbitrary 100 magic number.                                                                                                             
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             6. Remove any stray Javadoc comment lines (`* @throws java.io.IOException `) and unmatched `*/` tokens around the previous patch location. Ensure the Javadoc                      
                             comment preceding `public void dumpPictures(...)` remains correctly opened with `/**` and closed with `*/`, immediately above the method signature.                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             7. Rebalance braces: verify that each method (`dump`, `dumpPictures`, `main`, `write`, static `dump`) has matching `{}` and that the final `}` closes the                          
                             PPTXMLDump class.                                                                                                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             8. Run `javac` on poi-scratchpad after patch to confirm there are no syntax errors. The build should now succeed, and the fuzzer harness (which calls `dump(...)`)                  
                             remains unchanged and continues to cap record and picture data, preventing hangs on large or corrupted inputs.                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Justification:                                                                                                                                                                      
                             - Removing the faulty stub eliminates the source of illegal start of expression due to unmatched Javadoc delimiters.                                                              
                             - Using the existing `dump(Writer,)` keeps the codepath unified, avoids duplicating hexdump logic, and retains all helper methods.                                               
                             - Introducing a MAX_DUMP constant normalizes the cap across both record and picture dumps.                                                                                          
                             - The earlyexit checks preserve original functionality (full dump of valid data) but guard against reading past buffer bounds and infinite loops, addressing the                   
                             initial libFuzzer timeout issue.                                                                                                                                                    
                             - No harness code or external libraries are modified; only PPTXMLDump.java is touched.                                                                                              
                             - Existing tests and examples that rely on `dump` semantics remain valid; this patch merely limits unbounded output, which is acceptable for a debug/dump tool.                     
                             - This approach has minimal side effects: small metadata dumps are unaffected; large or corrupted streams are truncated rather than hung.                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                     
                             ===Evaluation End===

                             ===Patch Result===                                                                                                                                                                  
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ===Issue===                                                                                                                                                                         
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                                                                                             
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Summary                                                                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             The initial issue is a libFuzzer run aborting with a timeout error when exercising the PPTXMLDump component of the Apache POI Scratchpad. A patch attempt was made                  
                             against `src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hslf/dev/PPTXMLDump.java` to introduce a maximum dump limit (`MAX_DUMP`) and to add several early-exit guard checks in the                    
                             record-dumping loop. After applying that patch, the fuzzer still reports the same timeout error.                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Description                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Initial Issue                                                                                                                                                                       
                             - The fuzzer invocation terminates with ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout, indicating that during fuzzed inputs the target code took too long or entered a                                
                             non-terminating path.                                                                                                                                                               
                             - No stack trace or other errors are reportedonly the timeout condition from libFuzzer.                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Patch Attempt                                                                                                                                                                       
                             - A new constant `private static final int MAX_DUMP = 1024;` was added near the top of `PPTXMLDump.java`.                                                                           
                             - Inside the main `dump(byte[] data, int offset, int length, int padding)` loop:                                                                                                    
                               - Computed `remainingBytes = offset + length - pos` and break out of the loop if fewer than `HEADER_SIZE` bytes remain.                                                           
                               - Changed the check on record header size from `if (size < 0)` to `if (size <= 0)` and replaced `continue` with `break`.                                                          
                               - Added a further guard `if (size > remaining) { break; }` to avoid processing oversized records.                                                                                 
                             - In the atom-data dumping branches:                                                                                                                                                
                               - Replaced hardcoded `100`-byte dumps with `MAX_DUMP`.                                                                                                                            
                               - Updated two sites where atom and image data were truncated to the first 100 bytes; both now use `Math.min(size, Math.min(data.length-pos, MAX_DUMP))`.                          
                             - After applying these changes verbatim to the file, running the same fuzz target yielded the identical ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout result.                                         
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Post-Patch Log                                                                                                                                                                      
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Areas for Further Investigation                                                                                                                                                     
                             - The looping and recursion within `PPTXMLDump.dump(...)`, particularly how deeply nested records are handled and whether the early-exit guards cover all edge                      
                             cases.                                                                                                                                                                              
                             - The interactions in the `dump(Writer, byte[], int, int, int, boolean)` helper method, which may be consuming excessive time on large or malformed input blobs.                    
                             - The handling of picture data sections (`<picture>`, `<imgdata>`), where image payloads can be large and where additional parsing or decoding might be triggered.                  
                             - Any auxiliary code that the fuzzer invokes before or after `PPTXMLDump` (e.g., the harness setup) to ensure no other part of the codebase is contributing to the                  
                             timeout.                                                                                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Initial Issue Log                                                                                                                                                                
                             Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                                                                                                                      
                             <issue>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </issue>                                                                                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Additional Issue Log                                                                                                                                                             
                             Here is the additional issue log after the last patch attempt:                                                                                                                      
                             <additional_issue>                                                                                                                                                                  
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </additional_issue>                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Notes                                                                                                                                                                            
                             - All patch attempts are applied to the initial codebase. Reapply the the previous patches if needed.                                                                               
                             - If multiple different issues are present, all the issues must be resolved in a single patch attempt.                                                                              
                             - Try different approaches to resolve the issues.

                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             112:    public void dump(byte[] data, int offset, int length, int padding) throws IOException {                                                                                     
                             113:        int pos = offset;                                                                                                                                                       
                             114:        while (pos <= (offset + length - HEADER_SIZE)){                                                                                                                         
                             115:            if (pos < 0) {                                                                                                                                                      
                             116:                break;                                                                                                                                                          
                             117:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             118:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             119:            //read record header                                                                                                                                                
                             120:            int info = LittleEndian.getUShort(data, pos);                                                                                                                       
                             121:            pos += LittleEndianConsts.SHORT_SIZE;                                                                                                                               
                             122:            int type = LittleEndian.getUShort(data, pos);                                                                                                                       
                             123:            pos += LittleEndianConsts.SHORT_SIZE;                                                                                                                               
                             124:            int size = (int)LittleEndian.getUInt(data, pos);                                                                                                                    
                             125:            pos += LittleEndianConsts.INT_SIZE;                                                                                                                                 
                             126:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             127:            if (size < 0) {                                                                                                                                                     
                             128:                // stop processing of invalid header data                                                                                                                       
                             129:                continue;                                                                                                                                                       
                             130:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             131:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             132:            //get name of the record by type                                                                                                                                    
                             133:            String recname = RecordTypes.forTypeID(type).name();                                                                                                                
                             134:            write(out, "<"+recname + " info=\""+info+"\" type=\""+type+"\" size=\""+size+"\" offset=\""+(pos-8)+"\"", padding);                                                 
                             135:            if (hexHeader){                                                                                                                                                     
                             136:                out.write(" header=\"");                                                                                                                                        
                             137:                dump(out, data, pos-8, 8, 0, false);                                                                                                                            
                             138:                out.write("\"");                                                                                                                                                
                             139:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             140:            out.write(">" + CR);                                                                                                                                                
                             141:            padding++;                                                                                                                                                          
                             142:            //this check works both for Escher and PowerPoint records                                                                                                           
                             143:            boolean isContainer = (info & 0x000F) == 0x000F;                                                                                                                    
                             144:            if (isContainer) {                                                                                                                                                  
                             145:                //continue to dump child records                                                                                                                                
                             146:                dump(data, pos, size, padding);                                                                                                                                 
                             147:            } else {                                                                                                                                                            
                             148:                //dump first 100 bytes of the atom data                                                                                                                         
                             149:                dump(out, data, pos, Math.min(size, data.length-pos), padding, true);                                                                                           
                             150:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             151:            padding--;                                                                                                                                                          
                             152:            write(out, "</"+recname + ">" + CR, padding);                                                                                                                       
                             153:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             154:            pos += size;                                                                                                                                                        
                             155:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             156:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             ```

                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             165:    public void dumpPictures(byte[] data, int padding) throws IOException {                                                                                                     
                             166:        int pos = 0;                                                                                                                                                            
                             167:        while (pos < data.length) {                                                                                                                                             
                             168:            if(data.length - pos < PICT_HEADER_SIZE) {                                                                                                                          
                             169:                // corrupt file, cannot read header                                                                                                                             
                             170:                return;                                                                                                                                                         
                             171:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             172:            byte[] header = Arrays.copyOfRange(data, pos, pos + PICT_HEADER_SIZE);                                                                                              
                             173:            int size = LittleEndian.getInt(header, 4) - 17;                                                                                                                     
                             174:            if(size < 0) {                                                                                                                                                      
                             175:                // corrupt file, negative image size                                                                                                                            
                             176:                return;                                                                                                                                                         
                             177:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             178:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             179:            pos += PICT_HEADER_SIZE + size;                                                                                                                                     
                             180:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             181:            padding++;                                                                                                                                                          
                             182:            write(out, "<picture size=\""+size+"\" type=\""+getPictureType(header)+"\">" + CR, padding);                                                                        
                             183:            padding++;                                                                                                                                                          
                             184:            write(out, "<header>" + CR, padding);                                                                                                                               
                             185:            dump(out, header, 0, header.length, padding, true);                                                                                                                 
                             186:            write(out, "</header>" + CR, padding);                                                                                                                              
                             187:            write(out, "<imgdata>" + CR, padding);                                                                                                                              
                             188:            dump(out, data, 0, Math.min(size, 100), padding, true);                                                                                                             
                             189:            write(out, "</imgdata>" + CR, padding);                                                                                                                             
                             190:            padding--;                                                                                                                                                          
                             191:            write(out, "</picture>" + CR, padding);                                                                                                                             
                             192:            padding--;                                                                                                                                                          
                             193:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             194:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             ```

                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hslf/dev/PPTXMLDump.java:253-271                                                                                                        
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             253:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             254:     *  dump binary data to {@code out} with the specified padding                                                                                                              
                             255:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             256:    private static void dump(Writer out, byte[] data, int offset, int length, int padding, boolean nl) throws IOException {                                                     
                             257:        int linesize = 25;                                                                                                                                                      
                             258:        for (int i = 0; i < padding; i++) out.write("  ");                                                                                                                      
                             259:        int i;                                                                                                                                                                  
                             260:        for (i = offset; i < (offset + length); i++) {                                                                                                                          
                             261:            int c = data[i];                                                                                                                                                    
                             262:            out.write((char) hexval[(c & 0xF0) >> 4]);                                                                                                                          
                             263:            out.write((char) hexval[(c & 0x0F) >> 0]);                                                                                                                          
                             264:            out.write(' ');                                                                                                                                                     
                             265:            if((i+1-offset) % linesize == 0 && i != (offset + length-1)) {                                                                                                      
                             266:                out.write(CR);                                                                                                                                                  
                             267:                for (int j = 0; j < padding; j++) out.write("  ");                                                                                                              
                             268:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             269:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             270:        if(nl && length > 0)out.write(CR);                                                                                                                                      
                             271:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             ```
